<TITLE> Clash erupt between BCL factions at DU </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com)  Violence erupted between two groups of Bangladesh Chhatra Leaguethe pro-ruling Awami League student bodyat Dhaka University's Haji Mohammad Mohsin Hall leaving at least one injured on Tuesday. Clashes occurred between a faction led by BCL president Mohammad Ali and a rival group led by general secretary Mohammad Mohiuddin at around 1:30am. The injured, Mohibullah, was first taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital and later shifted to DU medical centre. BCL president Ali told bdnews24.com his rival group attacked his supporters with knifes and iron rods as they were trying to give Mohibullah shelter in a hall room. The rival group also fired blank shots, he alleged. BCL general secretary Mohiuddin claimed that his rival group was giving shelter to Chhatra Dal and Shibir activists to help them in 'tender terrorism'. As general students tried to obstruct them from providing shelter to Mohibullah, who Mohiuddin claimed was a former JCD activist, the clash ensued. Hall provost Ali Akhter told bdnews24.com he called police as soon as he heard about the clash. Shahbagh police chief Rezaul Karim said they had raided the hall after the clash and recovered knifes and rods. DU assistant proctor Amzad Ali said the incident of firing occurred in the campus after a long time. "We have taken the issue seriously. We will decide on how to free the campus from arms," he said. bdnews24
